<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1399,450,511]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
The specific epithet refers to the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morassi &amp; Nappo &amp; Bonfitto" authorityYear="2017" box="[658,748,450,476]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Otitoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[658,748,450,476]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, meaning ‘characterized by refined grace’, alluding to the aesthetically pleasant appearance of the shell.
</paragraph>
